I think the city manager form of government is bad 
for Texas. This may seem heresy. The city manager

07:17.020 --> 07:39.625
form of government views planning as, in this 
metropolitan area, they view planning as

07:17.020 --> 07:39.625
subservient

07:17.020 --> 07:39.625
to their office of being coordinator and they 
frequently override planners'

07:17.020 --> 07:39.625
recommendations. So as far as being an effective 
form of government to create urban change for the

07:41.107 --> 07:49.960
future, it doesn't. It's reactive to business 
interests and resident interests. So it becomes

07:55.968 --> 08:00.495
reactive as opposed to proactive. Planning must 
be proactive. There is an institutional conflict

08:03.199 --> 08:08.346
there between planning and city manager form of 
government. You'd rather see a strong mayor type?

08:11.792 --> 08:12.633
Yes, indeed. Yes, indeed. That's what El Paso has, 
and it has worked quite well there, because what

08:15.476 --> 08:32.291
that has done, in the case of John Cunningham, was 
to put him in the position of being a de facto city

08:15.476 --> 08:32.291
manager, as well as planning director. Now, under 
I don't mean even... And as to Valencia, we'll have

08:37.891 --> 08:45.884
to see what role planning has to play under a new 
personality.

